'''Dutch Golden Age Highlights''' is a special exhibition at the [[Rijksmuseum]] drawing on the museum's holdings of 17th-century Dutch art. It brings together masterworks of painting, drawing, and decorative art from the period when the Dutch Republic dominated European trade and culture.

Featured works include pieces by [[Johannes Vermeer]] and other leading masters of the era, grouped thematically to trace the social and economic context of the Republic's golden century.
